<span class="displaytext">chicago, il-senator (candidate last) today released the following statement on vice president cheney's attempts to prevent public scrutiny of his office. <p>"throughout this administration, vice president cheney has consistently sought to operate in secrecy and thwart rules designed to ensure the public's right to know how their business is being done. i believe strongly that democracy works best when it does its work in the daylight. in an (candidate last) administration, we will launch the most sweeping ethics reform in history so that we can restore an open, honest government that finally makes real progress on the challenges facing the american people."</p></span>



